+## Plan Checkbox State (resume-safe progress log)
+
+The plan file's `- [ ]` / `- [x]` checkboxes are the durable, cross-session record of what's done. The controller (you) is responsible for keeping them accurate.
+
+**At plan load (before dispatching anything):**
+1. `grep -nE '^- \[(x| )\]' <plan-file>` to enumerate every step and its state.
+2. For every step already `- [x]`: mark its TodoWrite todo as completed and never include that step in any implementer prompt. The implementer must not see done steps in its task description.
+3. If every step in a task is `- [x]`, that task is done — skip it entirely. Move to the next task with pending steps.
+4. If checkbox state is internally inconsistent (later steps `- [x]` while earlier steps in the same task are `- [ ]`, or `- [x]` next to obviously missing artifacts on disk), pause and surface this to the human partner before starting. Do NOT silently re-run or "trust the checkboxes".
+5. Pending steps (`- [ ]`) seed the TodoWrite list and the implementer prompts.
+
+**After a task passes spec review + code quality review + prose cleanup (and BEFORE marking the TodoWrite todo complete):**
+1. Edit the plan file: flip every `- [ ]` belonging to that task's steps to `- [x]`. Use Edit on the literal `- [ ]` prefix per step line. Do not reformat surrounding lines.
+2. Commit the plan file edit (alongside any final cleanup commits, or as its own commit). The commit message can be terse: `plan: mark Task N complete`.
+3. Then mark the TodoWrite todo complete and proceed to the next task.
+
+**If the implementer reported flipping individual step boxes during execution (it should — see implementer-prompt.md):**
+- Verify the boxes match what was actually implemented before you start review. A `- [x]` next to unverified work is a bug; flip it back and re-run.
+- Do NOT double-flip steps the implementer already flipped. Only flip ones still `- [ ]`.
+
+**Never:**
+- Author or accept new pre-checked `- [x]` boxes (those are skip-this signals; manufacturing them skips real work).
+- Batch all flips at the end of the whole plan — the resume point is lost.
+- Touch unrelated checkboxes in the plan file.
